<item>
            <title>[FELIX-2915] Potential deadlock on shutdown</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-2915</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As noted in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SLING-2051&quot; title=&quot;Sling does not shut down cleanly on Windows Server 2008&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SLING-2051&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SLING-2051&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; there are situations where a deadlock on shutdown occurs - this is because the thread pool is waiting for shutdown and blocks the framework&lt;br/&gt;
The pool can&apos;t be properly shutdown as event handlers might be already down (this is an unfortunate but expected behaviour)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The pool shut not wait for shutdown&lt;/p&gt;</description>
